gomodel:SYNGO_2675  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Arg is localized and enriched at dendritic spines\"\n- \"Arg-RFP was selectively enriched in >90% of dendritic spines, while co-expressed green fluorescent protein (GFP) was found at comparable levels in both dendritic spines and dendrite shafts (Fig. 1A, B).\"\n- \"Although Arg-RFP localizes predominantly to the post-synaptic compartment, shown by its colocalization with the postsynaptic marker PSD-95 (Fig. 1F), residual levels of Arg have also been localized to presynaptic terminals (Moresco et al., 2003; Sfakianos et al., 2007)\". Experimental description: - \"Balb/c mice were purchased from Charles River Laboratories...\"\n- Species of overexpressed Abl2 is not stated in the paper nor in the referenced M&M of PMID:15138293. Authors were contacted for information (dd 21/2/2018, anthony.koleske@yale.edu). Answer:\n\"Hi Pim\nThank you for doing this. It was mouse Abl2.\nTony\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2675" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

